<PB REF="00000078.tif" N="66"></L>
<L>And &yogh;et it were a game to here it al</L>
<L>To him &thorn;at meneth wel it were no charge</L>
<L N="2288">But it is good a man be at his large</L>
<L>hir brighte her was kempt vntressed al</L>
<L>A Corone of a grene Ok cerial</L>
<L>vpon hir heed was set ful fair and meete</L>
<L N="2292">Tuo fyres on &thorn;e auter gan sche beete</L>
<L>And did hir &thorn;inges as men may biholde</L>
<L>In state of Thebes and &thorn;e bokes olde</L>
<L>whan kynled was &thorn;e fyre wi&thorn; pitous cheere /</L>
<L N="2296">vnto Dyan sche spak as &yogh;e may heere</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ochaste goddes of &thorn;e woodes greene</L>
<L>To whom bo&thorn;e heuen and er&thorn;e and see is seene</L>
<L>Queen of &thorn;e regne of pluto derk and lowe</L>
<L N="2300">Goddes of maydenes &thorn;at myn hert has knowe</L>
<L>Ful many a &yogh;eer / &yogh;e woot what I desire</L>
<L>As keep me fro &thorn;e vengans of &thorn;ilk yre</L>
<L>That atheon aboughte trewely</L>
<L N="2304">Chaste goddesse wel wost &thorn;ou &thorn;at I</L>
<L>Desire to ben a mayden al my lyf</L>
<L>Ne neuer wol I be no loue ne wyf</L>
<L>I am &yogh;it &thorn;ou wost of &thorn;i company</L>
<L N="2308">A mayden and loue huntyng and venery</L>
<L>And for to walken in &thorn;e woodes wylde</L>
<L>And nought to ben a wyf and be with chylde</L>
