<L>That al here hoote loue and here desire</L>
<L N="2320">Al here besy torment and al here fyre</L>
<L>Be queynt or turned in ano&thorn;er place
<PB REF="00000079.tif" N="67"></L>
<L>And if so be &thorn;ou wol do me no grace</L>
<L>Or if my destyne be schapid so<MILESTONE N="31b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2324">That I schal needes haue on of hem two</L>
<L>So send me him &thorn;at most desire&thorn; me</L>
<L>Biholde goddes of clene chastite</L>
<L>The bitter teeres &thorn;at on my cheekes falle</L>
<L N="2328">Syn &thorn;ou art mayde and keper of vs alle</L>
<L>My maydenhode &thorn;ou kepe and wel conserue</L>
<L>And whil I lyue a mayde I wil &thorn;e serue /</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>The fyres bren vpon &thorn;e auter cleer</L>
<L N="2332">whil Emelye was in hire preyer</L>
<L>But sodeinly sche saugh a sighte queynt</L>
