<L>And wepte &thorn;at/ it was pite to heere</L>
<L>And &thorn;er-wi&thorn;-al Dyane gan appeere</L>
<L>wi&thorn; bow in hond right as a hunteresse</L>
<L N="2348">And seyd a doughter stynt &thorn;yn heuynesse</L>
<L>Among &thorn;e goddes hye it is affermed</L>
<L>And by eterne word write &amp; confermed</L>
<L>Thou schalt be wedded vnto oon of &thorn;o</L>
<L N="2352">That haue for &thorn;e so moche care and wo</L>
<L>But vnto which of hem may I nat telle</L>
<L>Far wel for I may her no lenger dwelle</L>
<L>The fyres which &thorn;at on myn auter bren</L>
<L N="2356">Schuln &thorn;e declare or &thorn;at &thorn;ou go hen</L>
<L>Thyn aduenture of loue and in &thorn;is caas
<PB REF="00000080.tif" N="68"></L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word &thorn;e arwes in &thorn;e caas</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e goddesse clatren faste and rynge</L>
<L N="2360">And for&thorn; sche went and made a vanysschynge</L>
<L>For which this Emelye astoneyd was<MILESTONE N="32a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And seide what amounte&thorn; &thorn;is allas</L>
