<L>And hoom sche go&thorn; anon &thorn;e nexte way</L>
<L>This is &thorn;effect/ &thorn;er nys no mor to say</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>The nexte houre of mars folwynge &thorn;is</L>
<L N="2368">Arcite to &thorn;e temple walkyd is /</L>
<L>To fyry mars to doon his sacrifise /</L>
<L>with al &thorn;e rightes of his payen wise</L>
<L>with pitous herte and heih deuocioun</L>
<L N="2372">Right thus to mars he sayd his orisoun</L>
<L>O stronge god &thorn;at in &thorn;e reynes cold</L>
<L>Of trace honoured and lord art &thorn;ou hold</L>
<L>And hast in euery regne and euery land</L>
<L N="2376">Of armes al &thorn;e bridel in &thorn;y hand</L>
<L>And hem fortunest as &thorn;e lust deuyse</L>
<L>Accept/ of me my pitous sacrifise</L>
<L>If so be &thorn;at my &yogh;outhe may deserue</L>
<L N="2380">And &thorn;at my might be wor&thorn;i to deserue</L>
<L>Thy godhed &thorn;at/ I may be on of &thorn;ine</L>
<L>Then pray I &thorn;e / to rewe on my pyne</L>
<L>For &thorn;ilke peyne and &thorn;at hoote fuyre</L>
<L N="2384">The which whilom &thorn;ou brendest for desyre</L>
<L>whan &thorn;at &thorn;ou vsedest &thorn;e gret bewte</L>
<L>Of faire freissche Venus &thorn;at is so free</L>
<L>And haddest hir in armes at &thorn;y wille</L>
<L N="2388">And &thorn;ough &thorn;e ones on a tyme mysfille</L>
<L>whan Vlcanus had caught &thorn;e in his laas</L>
<L>And fand &thorn;e liggyng by his wyf allaas</L>
<L>For &thorn;ilke sorwe &thorn;at was in &thorn;in herte</L>
<L N="2392">haue reuthe as wel vpon my peynes smerte</L>
<L>I am &yogh;ong and vnkonnyng as &thorn;ou wost
<PB REF="00000081.tif" N="69"></L>
<L>And as I trowe / wi&thorn; loue offendid most /</L>
<L>That euer was eny lyues creature /</L>
<L N="2396">For sche &thorn;at doth me / al &thorn;is wo endure</L>
<L>Ne rekke&thorn; neuer whe&thorn;er I synke or flete</L>
<L>And wel I woot or sche me mercy heete</L>
<L>I moot wi&thorn; streng&thorn;e wyn hir in &thorn;e place<MILESTONE N="32b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2400">And wel I wot/ wi&thorn;outen help or grace</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e / ne may my strengthe nought auayle</L>
