<L>And &thorn;us with ioye and hope wel to fare</L>
<L N="2436">Arcite anoon / vnto his Inne is fare /</L>
<L>As fayn as foul is of &thorn;e brighte sonne<MILESTONE N="33a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And right anon such stryf is bygonne</L>
<L>For &thorn;at grauntyng in &thorn;e heuen aboue</L>
<L N="2440">Bitwix venus and &thorn;e goddes of loue</L>
<L>And marcz &thorn;e sterne god armypotent</L>
<L>That Iupiter was busy it to stent</L>
<L>Til &thorn;at &thorn;e pale Saturnes &thorn;e colde</L>
<L N="2444">That knew so many of auentures olde</L>
<L>Fond in his experiens an art/</L>
<L>That he ful sone ha&thorn; plesyd euery part</L>
<L>And so&thorn; is sayd eelde ha&thorn; gret auantage</L>
<L N="2448">In eelde is bo&thorn;e wisdom and vsage</L>
<L>Men may &thorn;e eelde at-ren but nat at-rede</L>
<L>Saturne anon to stynte stryf and drede</L>
<L>Al be it &thorn;at / it be agayns his kynde</L>
<L N="2452">Of al &thorn;is stryf he can remedy fynde</L>
<L>My deere dou&yogh;ter venus quod Satourne</L>
