<L N="3036">The which is prynce and cuase of alle thing</L>
<L>Conuertyng al vnto his propre wille</L>
<L>From which he is dereyned so&thorn; to telle /
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="87"></L>
<L>And here agayn no creature of lyue</L>
<L N="3040">Of no degre auayle&thorn; for to stryue</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Than is it wisdom as &thorn;enke&thorn; me</L>
<L>To maken vertu of necessite</L>
<L>And take it wel &thorn;at we may nat eschewe</L>
<L N="3044">And namely &thorn;at &thorn;at to vs alle is dewe /</L>
<L>And who-so grucche&thorn; aught he do&thorn; folye</L>
<L>And rebel is to him &thorn;at al may gye<MILESTONE N="41a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And certeynly a man ha&thorn; most honour</L>
<L N="3048">To deyen in his excellence and flour</L>
<L>whan he is siker of his goode name</L>
<L>Than ha&thorn; he doon his freend ne him no schame</L>
<L>And gladder ought his freend ben of his de&thorn;</L>
<L N="3052">whan with honour is &yogh;olden vp &thorn;e breth</L>
<L>Thanne whan his name appeled is for age</L>
