<L>That had almost . as lief to leese hir necke /</L>
<L>As for to &yogh;iue a peny of hir good</L>
<L N="1576">I wolf pens &thorn;ough &thorn;at sche go wood</L>
<L>Or I wol somone hir to oure office<MILESTONE N="107a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And &yogh;it god wot I know of hir no vice</L>
<L>But for &thorn;ou canst not as in &thorn;is contre</L>
<L N="1580">wynne &thorn;y cost tak/ her ensample of me
<PB REF="00000252.tif" N="240"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="380"></L>
<L>This sompnour clapped at &thorn;e widowes gate</L>
<L>Com out quod he &thorn;ou olde viritrate</L>
