<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000255.tif" N="243">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="383">
<HEAD>&para; And here begynneth &thorn;e sompnour his prologe</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>This sompnour in his styrop vp he stood</L>
<L>vpon &thorn;e Frere his herte was so wood</L>
<L>That lyk an aspen leef/ he quok for Ire</L>
<L N="1668">lordyngs quod he . but oon &thorn;ing I desire</L>
<L>I &yogh;ow biseke &thorn;at of &yogh;our curtesye</L>
<L>Syn &yogh;e han herd &thorn;is false frere lye</L>
<L>As suffrith me I may my tale telle</L>
<L N="1672">This frere bosteth &thorn;at he knowith helle</L>
<L>And god it wot . &thorn;at is litil wonder</L>
<L>Freres and feendes been but litel asonder</L>
<L>For pardy &yogh;e han often tyme herd telle /</L>
<L N="1676">how &thorn;at a frere rauyscht was to helle</L>
<L>In spirit ones by a visioun</L>
<L>And as an aungel . lad him vp and doun</L>
<L>To schewen him &thorn;e peynes &thorn;at &thorn;er were</L>
<L N="1680">In al &thorn;e place saugh he not a frere</L>
<L>Of o&thorn;er folk he saugh ynowe in wo</L>
<L>vnto &thorn;is aungel spak &thorn;is frere &thorn;o</L>
<L>Now sire quod he han freres such a grace</L>
<L N="1684">That noon of hem schal comen in &thorn;is place</L>
<L>&YOGH;is quod &thorn;is aungil many a mylioun</L>
<L>And vnto Sathanas he lad him doun</L>
<L>And now ha&thorn; sathanas saith he a tayl</L>
<L N="1688">Broder &thorn;an of a Carrik is &thorn;e sayl</L>
<L>hold vp &thorn;y tayl &thorn;ou Sathanas quod he<MILESTONE N="108b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Schew forth &thorn;yn ars and let &thorn;e frere se</L>
<L>wher is &thorn;e nest of freres in &thorn;is place</L>
<L N="1692">And er &thorn;an half a forlong way of space
<PB REF="00000256.tif" N="244"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="384"></L>
<L>Right so as bees swarmen out of an hyue</L>
<L>Out of &thorn;e deueles ers &thorn;ay gonne dryue</L>
<L>Twenty &thorn;ousand freres on a route</L>
<L N="1696">And &thorn;orugh out helle swarmed al aboute</L>
<L>And comen as fast as &thorn;ay may goon</L>
<L>And in his ers &thorn;ay crepen euerich oon &middot;</L>
<L>he clappid his tayl agayn and lay ful stille</L>
<L N="1700">This frere whan he loked had his fille</L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;e torment of &thorn;is sory place</L>
<L>his spirit god restored of his grace</L>
<L>vnto his body agayn and he awook</L>
<L N="1704">But na&thorn;eles for fere &yogh;it he quook</L>
<L>So was &thorn;e deueles ers &yogh;it in his mynde</L>
<L>That is his heritage of verray kynde/</L>
<L>God saue &yogh;ow alle saue &thorn;is cursed frere</L>
<L N="1708">My proloug wol I ende in &thorn;is manere<NOTE PLACE="end">[No break in the MS.]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
