<L>And dronkenes is eek a foul record</L>
<L>Of any man and namly of a lord</L>
<L>Ther is ful many ey&yogh;e and many an eere</L>
<L N="2052">Awaytand on a lord and he not where</L>
<L>For goddes loue drynk more attemperelly</L>
<L>wyn makith man to lese wrecchedly</L>
<L>his mynde and eek. his lymes euerichoon</L>
<L N="2056">The reuers schaltow seen quod he anoon</L>
<L>And proue it by &thorn;in owne experience</L>
<L>That wyn ne do&thorn; to folk non such offence</L>
<L>Ther is no wyn. byreueth me my wit</L>
<L N="2060">Of hond of foot ne of myn ey&yogh;e sight
<PB REF="00000267.tif" N="255"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="395"></L>
<L>And for despyt he dronke moche more<MILESTONE N="113b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>An hundrid part &thorn;an he had doon byfore</L>
<L>And right anoon &thorn;is irous cursid wrecche /</L>
<L N="2064">Let &thorn;is knightes sone anoon biforn him fecche</L>
<L>Comaundyng hem &thorn;ay schuld biforn him stonde</L>
<L>And sodeinly he took his bowe on honde</L>
<L>And vp &thorn;e streng he pulled to his eere</L>
<L N="2068">And wi&thorn; an arwe he slough &thorn;e child right &thorn;ere</L>
<L>Now whe&thorn;ir haue I a sikur hond or noon</L>
<L>Quod he is al my mynde and might agoon</L>
<L>hath wyn byreuyd me myn eye sight</L>
<L N="2072">what schuld I telle &thorn;e answer of &thorn;e knight</L>
<L>his sone was slayn &thorn;er is no more to say</L>
<L>Be war &thorn;erfor. wi&thorn; lordes how &yogh;e play</L>
<L>Syngith placebo. and I schal if I can</L>
<L N="2076">But if it be. vnto a pore man</L>
<L>To a pore man men schuld his vices telle</L>
<L>But not to a lord &thorn;ey he schuld go to helle</L>
<L>lo Irous Cirus &thorn;ilke Percien</L>
<L N="2080">how he destruyed &thorn;e ryuer of Gysen</L>
<L>For &thorn;at an hors of his was dreynt &thorn;er Inne.</L>
<L>whan &thorn;at he wente Babiloyne to wynne</L>
<L>he made &thorn;at &thorn;e ryuer was so smal</L>
<L N="2084">&THORN;at wommen mighte wade it ouer al</L>
<L>lo what sayde he &thorn;at so wel teche can</L>
<L>Ne be no felaw . to an irous man</L>
<L>Ne with no wood man walke by &thorn;e way</L>
<L N="2088">lest &thorn;e repent I wol no lenger say</L>
<L>Now thomas leue bro&thorn;er leue &thorn;in Ire</L>
<L>Thow schalt me fynde as iust as is a squire</L>
<L>Thyn anger doth &thorn;e al to sore smerte</L>
<L N="2092">hald not &thorn;e deueles knyf alway at &thorn;yn herte</L>
<L>But schewe to me al &thorn;y confessioun</L>
<L>Nay quod &thorn;is syke man by seynt symoun</L>
<L>I haue ben schriuen &thorn;is day of my curate</L>
<L N="2096">I haue him told holly al myn estate/
<PB REF="00000268.tif" N="256"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="396"></L>
<L>Nedith no more to speken of it saith he /</L>
<L>But if me list of myn humilite.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if me &thorn;an of &thorn;y good to make our cloyster<MILESTONE N="114a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2100">Quod he for many a muscle and many an oyster</L>
<L>ha&thorn; ben oure foode our Cloyster to arreyse</L>
<L>whan o&thorn;er men han ben ful wel at eyse</L>
<L>And &yogh;it god wot vnnethe &thorn;e foundement</L>
<L N="2104">Parformed is ne of oure pauyment</L>
<L>Is nought a tyle &yogh;it wi&thorn;inne our wones</L>
<L>By god we owe &yogh;it fourty pound for stones</L>
<L>Now help Thomas for him &thorn;at harewed helle</L>
<L N="2108">Or elles moote we oure bookes selle</L>
<L>And &yogh;if &yogh;ow lakke oure predicacioun</L>
<L>Thanne go&thorn; &thorn;e world al to destruccioun</L>
<L>For who-so wold vs fro &thorn;e world byreue</L>
<L N="2112">So god me saue Thomas by &yogh;oure leue</L>
<L>he wolde byreue out of &thorn;is world &thorn;e sonne</L>
<L>For who can teche. and werken as we conne</L>
<L>And &thorn;is is not of litel tyme quod he</L>
<L N="2116">But si&thorn;&thorn;en Elye was her or ele</L>
<L>han freres ben fynde I of record</L>
<L>In charite I-&thorn;anked be oure lord</L>
<L>Now Thomas help for seynte charite</L>
<L N="2120">A-doun he sette him anoon on his kne</L>
<L>This sike man wex welneigh wood for Ire</L>
<L>he wolde &thorn;at &thorn;e frere had ben on fuyre</L>
<L>with his fals dissimulacioun</L>
<L N="2124">Such &thorn;ing as is in my possessioun</L>
<L>Quod he &thorn;at may I &yogh;eue &yogh;ow and noon o&thorn;er</L>
<L>&YOGH;e sayn me &thorn;us how &thorn;at I am &yogh;our bro&thorn;er</L>
<L>&YOGH;e certes quod &thorn;e frere trusteth wel</L>
<L N="2128">I took our dame &thorn;e letter vnder oure sel</L>
<L>Now wel quod he and som what schal I &yogh;iue</L>
<L>Vnto &yogh;our holy couent whils &thorn;at I lyue</L>
<L>And in &thorn;yn hond &thorn;ou schalt it haue anoon</L>
<L N="2132">On &thorn;is condicioun and o&thorn;er noon
<PB REF="00000269.tif" N="257"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="397"></L>
<L>That &thorn;ou depart it so my deere bro&thorn;er</L>
<L>That euery frere haue as moche as o&thorn;er</L>
<L>Thy schaltow swere on &thorn;y professioun</L>
<L N="2136">wi&thorn;outen fraude or cauillacioun</L>
<L>I swere it quod &thorn;is frere vpon my faith<MILESTONE N="114b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And &thorn;er-with his hond in his he laith</L>
<L>lo her myn hond in me schal be no lak</L>
<L N="2140">Now &thorn;anne put &thorn;yn hond doun at my bak</L>
<L>Sayde &thorn;is man and grope wel byhynde</L>
<L>Bynethe my buttok &thorn;ere schaltow fynde</L>
<L>A &thorn;ing &thorn;at I haue hud in priuete</L>
<L N="2144">A &thorn;ought &thorn;is frere &thorn;at schal go with me /</L>
<L>And doun his hond he launched to &thorn;e clifte</L>
<L>In hope for to fynde &thorn;er a &yogh;ifte</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;is syke man felte &thorn;is frere</L>
<L N="2148">Aboute his tuel grope &thorn;er and heere</L>
<L>Amyd his hond he leet &thorn;e freere a fart</L>
<L>Ther is no capul drawyng in a cart</L>
<L>That might haue let a fart of such a soun</L>
<L N="2152">The frere vpstart as doth a wood lyoun</L>
<L>A false cherl quod he for goddes bones</L>
<L>This hastow in despit don for &thorn;e noones</L>
<L>Thou schalt abye &thorn;is fart if &thorn;at I may</L>
<L N="2156">his meyne which &thorn;at herd of &thorn;is affray</L>
<L>Com lepand In and chased out &thorn;e frere</L>
<L>And forth he go&thorn; wi&thorn; a foul angry cheere</L>
<L>And fat his felaw &thorn;ere lay his stoor</L>
<L N="2160">he lokid as it were a wylde boor</L>
<L>And grynte with his tee&thorn; so was he wroth</L>
<L>A stordy paas doun to &thorn;e court he goth</L>
<L>wher as &thorn;er wonyd a man of gret honour</L>
<L N="2164">To whom &thorn;at he was alway confessour</L>
<L>This wor&thorn;y man was lord of &thorn;at / village</L>
<L>This frere com as he were in a rage</L>
<L>wher &thorn;at &thorn;is lord sat etyng at his bord</L>
<L N="2168">Vnne&thorn;e might &thorn;e frere speke a word
<PB REF="00000270.tif" N="258"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="398"></L>
<L>Til atte last he sayde god &yogh;ow se</L>
<L>This lord gan loke and sayde benedicite</L>
<L>What frere Iohn what maner world is &thorn;is /</L>
<L N="2172">I se wel. &thorn;at som &thorn;ing is amys</L>
<L>&YOGH;e loke as &thorn;ough &thorn;e woode were ful of &thorn;euys</L>
<L>Sit doun anoon and tel me what &yogh;our gref is</L>
<L>And it schal ben amendit if &thorn;at I may<MILESTONE N="115a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2176">I haue quod he had a despit to day</L>
<L>God &yogh;elde &yogh;ow a-doun in &yogh;oure vilage</L>
<L>That in &thorn;is world is noon so pore a page/</L>
<L>That he nold haue abhominacioun</L>
<L N="2180">Of &thorn;at I haue receyued in &yogh;oure toun</L>
<L>And &yogh;et ne greuith me no &thorn;ing so sore</L>
<L>As &thorn;at &thorn;is elde cherl wi&thorn; lokkes hore</L>
<L>Blasphemed ha&thorn; our holy couent eeke</L>
<L N="2184">Now maister quod &thorn;is lord I &yogh;ow biseke</L>
<L>No maister sir quod he but seruitour</L>
<L>&THORN;ough I haue had in scole such honour</L>
<L>God likith not &thorn;at Raby men vs calle</L>
<L N="2188">Neither in market neyther in &yogh;our large halle</L>
<L>No fors quod he tellith me al &yogh;our greef</L>
<L>&THORN;is frere sayd sire an odious meschief</L>
<L>This day bytid is to myn ordre and to me</L>
<L N="2192">And so par consequens to ech degre</L>
<L>Of holy chirche god amend it soone</L>
<L>Sir quod &thorn;e lord &yogh;e wot what is to doone</L>
<L>Distempre &yogh;ow nought &yogh;e ben my confessour</L>
<L N="2196">&YOGH;e ben &thorn;e salt of &thorn;er&thorn;e and sauyour</L>
<L>For goddes loue &yogh;oure pacience &yogh;e holde</L>
<L>Tel me &yogh;our greef and he anoon him tolde</L>
<L>As &yogh;e han herd bifore &yogh;e wot wel what</L>
<L N="2200">The lady of &thorn;at hous ay stille sat</L>
<L>Til sche had herd what &thorn;e frere sayde</L>
<L>Ey goddes moodir quod she blisful mayde</L>
<L>Is &thorn;er ought elles tel me faithfully</L>
<L N="2204">Ma dame quod he how &thorn;ynke &yogh;ow &thorn;erby
<PB REF="00000271.tif" N="259"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="399"></L>
<L>how &thorn;at me &thorn;ynkith quod sche so god me speede</L>
<L>I say a cherl ha&thorn; doon a cherles deede</L>
<L>what schuld I say god let him neuer &thorn;e</L>
<L N="2208">His syke heed is full of vanyte</L>
<L>I hold him in a maner frenesye /</L>
<L>Ma dame quod he I-wis I schal not lye</L>
<L>But I in o&thorn;ir wise may be wreke</L>
<L N="2212">I schal defame him ouer al wher I speke</L>
<L>The false blasfememour &thorn;at chargid me<MILESTONE N="115b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To parten &thorn;at wil not departed be</L>
<L>To euery man yliche wi&thorn; meschaunce</L>
<L N="2216">The lord sat stille as he were in a traunce</L>
<L>And in his hert he rollid vp and doun</L>
<L>How had &thorn;is cherl ymaginacioun</L>
<L>So schewe such a probleme to &thorn;e frere</L>
<L N="2220">Neuer eft er now herd I of such matiere</L>
<L>I trowe &thorn;e deuel put it in his mynde</L>
<L>In ars metrik / schal &thorn;er no man fynde</L>
<L>Biforn &thorn;is day of such a questioun</L>
<L N="2224">who schulde make a demonstracioun</L>
<L>That euery man schuld haue a lyk his part</L>
<L>As of a soun or of a sauour of a fart</L>
<L>O nyce proude cherl I schrew his face</L>
<L N="2228">lo sires quod &thorn;e lord wi&thorn; harde grace</L>
<L>who euer herde of such a &thorn;ing er now</L>
<L>To euery man y-like tel me how</L>
<L>It is impossible it may not be</L>
<L N="2232">Ey nyce cherl god let him neuer &thorn;e</L>
<L>The romblyng of a fart and euery soun</L>
<L>Nis but an aier reuerberacioun</L>
<L>And euer it wastith lyte and lyt away</L>
<L N="2236">Ther nys no man can deme by my fay /</L>
<L>If &thorn;at it were departed equally</L>
<L>what lo my cherl what lo how schrewedly</L>
<L>vnto my confessour to day he spak</L>
<L N="2240">I hold him certeinly demoniak
<PB REF="00000272.tif" N="260"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="400"></L>
<L>Now etith &yogh;our mete and let &thorn;e cherl go play /</L>
<L>Let him go honge himself on deuel way /<NOTE PLACE="inter">[The Solution of the "Probleme" by the Lord's Sguire. No break in the MS.]</NOTE></L>
<L>Now stood &thorn;e lordes squier at &thorn;e bord</L>
<L N="2244">That carf his mete and herde word by word</L>
<L>Of al &thorn;is &thorn;ing which &thorn;at I of haue sayd</L>
<L>My lord quod he be &yogh;e nou&yogh;t euel payd</L>
<L>I cou&thorn;e telle for a gowne cloth</L>
<L N="2248">To &yogh;ow sir frere so &thorn;at &yogh;e be not wroth</L>
<L>How &thorn;at &thorn;is fart euen / departed schuld be</L>
<L>Among &yogh;our couent if I comaunded be</L>
<L>Tel quod &thorn;e lord and &thorn;ou schalt haue anoon<MILESTONE N="116a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2252">A goune clo&thorn; by god and by seint Iohn</L>
<L>My lord quod he whan &thorn;at &thorn;e wedir is fair</L>
<L>wi&thorn;oute wynd or pertourbyng of ayr</L>
<L>let bring a large whel in to &thorn;is halle</L>
<L N="2256">But &thorn;at it haue his spokes alle</L>
<L>Twelf spokes hath a cart whel comunly</L>
<L>And bring me . xij . freres wit &yogh;e why</L>
<L>For &thorn;rettene is a couent as I gesse /</L>
<L N="2260">&YOGH;our noble confessour her god him blesse</L>
<L>Schal parfourn vp &thorn;e nombre of &thorn;is couent</L>
<L>Thanne schal &thorn;ay knele doun by oon assent</L>
<L>And to euery spokes ende in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L N="2264">Ful sadly lay his nose schal a frere</L>
<L>&YOGH;our noble confessour &thorn;er god him saue</L>
<L>Schal hold his nose vpright vnder &thorn;e naue</L>
<L>Than schal &thorn;is churl with bely stif and tought</L>
<L N="2268">As eny tabor hider ben y-brought</L>
<L>And sette him on &thorn;e whele of &thorn;is cart</L>
<L>vpon &thorn;e naue and make him lete a fart</L>
<L>And &yogh;e schul seen vp peril of my lif</L>
<L N="2272">By verray proef &thorn;at is demonstratif
<PB REF="00000273.tif" N="261"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="401"></L>
<L>That equally &thorn;e soun of it wol wende /</L>
<L>And eek &thorn;e stynk vnto &thorn;e spokes ende</L>
<L>Saue &thorn;at &thorn;is wor&thorn;y man &yogh;our confessour</L>
<L N="2276">By cause he is a man of gret honour</L>
<L>Schal haue &thorn;e firste fruyt as resoun is</L>
<L>The noble vsage of freres is &thorn;is</L>
<L>The worthy men of hem first schal be serued</L>
<L N="2280">As certeynly he ha&thorn; it wel deserued</L>
<L>he hath to day taught vs so mochil good</L>
<L>with preching in &thorn;e pulpit &thorn;er he stood</L>
<L>That I may vouche sauf I say for me</L>
<L N="2284">He hadde &thorn;e firste smel of fartes &thorn;re</L>
<L>And so wold al his couent hardily</L>
<L>he berith him so fair and holily</L>
<L>The lord &thorn;e lady and ech man sauf &thorn;e frere</L>
<L N="2288">Sayde &thorn;an Iankyn spak in &thorn;is matiere</L>
<L>As wel as euclide or elles protholome<MILESTONE N="116b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Touchand &thorn;e clerk &thorn;ay sayd &thorn;at subtilte</L>
<L>An high wyt made him speken as he spak</L>
<L N="2292">he nas no fool ne no demoniak /</L>
<L>And Iankyn ha&thorn; I-wonne a newe goune</L>
<L>My tale is don. we ben almost at toune.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>&para; Here endith the sompnours tale<NOTE PLACE="end">[No break in the MS.]</NOTE></TRAILER>
