<L>First loue of crist and to &yogh;our self honour</L>
<L N="2172">And al myn heritage toun and tour
<PB REF="00000340.tif" N="328"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="469"></L>
<L>I &yogh;iue it &yogh;ow makith chartres as &yogh;ow leste</L>
<L>This schal ben doon to morw er sonne reste</L>
<L>So wisly god my soule bringe in blisse</L>
<L N="2176">I pray &yogh;ow first in couenaunt &yogh;e me kisse</L>
<L>And &thorn;ough &thorn;at I be ialous wyt me nought</L>
<L>&YOGH;e ben so deep emprinted in my &thorn;ought</L>
<L>&THORN;at whan &thorn;at I considre &yogh;our beaute</L>
<L N="2180">And &thorn;er wi&thorn; al &thorn;e vnlikly eelde of me</L>
<L>I may nought certes &thorn;ough I schulde dye</L>
<L>Forbere to ben out of &yogh;our companye</L>
<L>For verray loue &thorn;is is wi&thorn;outen doute</L>
<L N="2184">Now kisse me wyf and let vs Rome aboute</L>
<L>This freissche may whan sche his worde herde</L>
<L>Benignely to Ianuary answerde /</L>
<L>But first and forward sche bigan to wepe</L>
<L N="2188">I haue quod sche a soule for to kepe<MILESTONE N="145b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>As wel as &yogh;e and also myn honour</L>
<L>And of my wifhod &thorn;ilke tendre flour</L>
<L>which &thorn;at I haue ensured in &yogh;our hond</L>
<L N="2192">whan &thorn;at &thorn;e prest to &yogh;ow my body bond</L>
<L>wherfor I wil answer in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>By &thorn;e leue of &yogh;ow my lord so deere</L>
<L>I pray to god &thorn;at neuer dawe &thorn;e day</L>
<L N="2196">That I ne sterue as foule as womman may</L>
<L>If euer I do to my kyn &thorn;at schame</L>
<L>Or elles I empaire so my name</L>
<L>That I be fals and if I do &thorn;at lak</L>
<L N="2200">Doth strepe me and put me in a sak</L>
<L>And in &thorn;e nexte ryuer do me drenche</L>
<L>I am a gentil womman and no wenche</L>
<L>why speke &yogh;e thus . but men ben euer vntrewe</L>
<L N="2204">And wommen han reproef of &yogh;ow euer newe</L>
<L>&YOGH;e haue noon o&thorn;er contenaunce I leue /</L>
<L>But speke to vs of vntrust and repreue</L>
<L>And with &thorn;at word sche saugh wher damyan</L>
<L N="2208">Sat in &thorn;e buissh and coughen sche bigan
<PB REF="00000341.tif" N="329"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="470"></L>
<L>And wi&thorn; hir fyngres signes made sche</L>
<L>That damyan schuld clymb vpon a tre<NOTE PLACE="marg">nota</NOTE></L>
<L>That charged was with fruyt/ and vp he went/</L>
<L N="2212">For verrayly he knew al hir entent</L>
<L>And euery signe &thorn;at sche couthe make</L>
<L>wel bet &thorn;an Ianuary hir oughne make</L>
<L>For in a letter sche had told him al</L>
<L N="2216">Of &thorn;is matier how he worche shal</L>
<L>And &thorn;us I lete him sitte vpon &thorn;e pirie</L>
<L>And Ianuary and may romynge mirye</L>
<L>&para; Bright was &thorn;e day and bliew &thorn;e firmament</L>
<L N="2220">Phebus ha&thorn; of gold his stremes doun I-sent</L>
<L>To gladen euery flour with his warmnesse</L>
<L>he was &thorn;at tyme in gemmes as I gesse</L>
<L>But litel fro his declinacioun</L>
<L N="2224">Of Caker . Ioues exaltacioun</L>
<L>And so bifel &thorn;at brighte morwen tyde</L>
<L>That in &thorn;at gardyn in &thorn;e ferther syde /<MILESTONE N="146a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Pluto that is kyng of fayerye</L>
<L N="2228">And many a lady in his compaignie</L>
<L>Folwyng his wif &thorn;e queene preserpine</L>
<L>Ech after o&thorn;er . as right as a lyne</L>
<L>whil &thorn;at sche gadred floures in &thorn;e mede</L>
<L N="2232">In claudian &yogh;e may &thorn;e story rede</L>
<L>how in &thorn;is grisly carte he hir fette</L>
<L>This king of fayry &thorn;an adoun him sette /</L>
<L>vpon a bench of turues freissh and greene</L>
<L N="2236">And right anoon &thorn;us sayd he to his queene /</L>
<L>&para; My wyf quod he &thorn;er may no wight say nay</L>
<L>Thexperiens so preueth euery day</L>
<L>The tresoun which &thorn;at womman doth to man</L>
<L N="2240">Ten hundrid &thorn;ousand . tellen I can</L>
<L>Notable of &yogh;our vntrouth and brutelnesse</L>
<L>O . Salamon wys and richest of richesse /</L>
<L>Fulfild of Sapiens . and of worldly glorie /</L>
<L N="2244">Ful wor&thorn;y ben &thorn;y wordes to memorie
<PB REF="00000342.tif" N="330"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="471"></L>
<L>To euery wight &thorn;at wit and resoun can</L>
<L>Thus praysith he &yogh;it &thorn;e bounte of man</L>
<L>Among a &thorn;ousand men &yogh;it fond I oon</L>
<L N="2248">But of wommen alle fond I noon</L>
<L>Thus saith &thorn;e king &thorn;at knoweth &yogh;our wikkednesse</L>
<L>And Ihc filius Sirac / as I gesse /</L>
<L>Ne spekith of &yogh;ow but selde reuerence</L>
<L N="2252">A. wilde fuyr and corrupt pestilence</L>
<L>So falle vpon &yogh;our bodies &yogh;it to night</L>
<L>Ne se &yogh;e not &thorn;is honurable knight</L>
<L>By cause allas &thorn;at he is blynd and old</L>
<L N="2256">his owne man schal make him cokewold</L>
<L>loo wher he sitt . &thorn;e lecchour in &thorn;e tre</L>
<L>Now wol I graunten of my maieste /</L>
<L>Unto &thorn;is olde blinde wor&thorn;y knight</L>
<L N="2260">&THORN;at he schal haue a&yogh;ein his ey&yogh;en sight</L>
<L>whan &thorn;at his wyf wol do him vilonye</L>
<L>Than schal he knowe al her harlotrye</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e in reproef of her and o&thorn;er mo</L>
<L N="2264">&YOGH;e schal quod preserpine and wol &yogh;e so<MILESTONE N="146b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Now by my modres sires soule I swere</L>
<L>That I schal &yogh;iue hir suffisaunt answere /</L>
<L>And alle wommen after for hir sake</L>
<L N="2268">That &thorn;ough &thorn;ay be in any gult I-take</L>
<L>with face bold &thorn;ay schul hemself excuse</L>
<L>And bere hem doun &thorn;at wolde hem accuse</L>
<L>For lak/ of answer noon of hem schal dyen</L>
<L N="2272">Al had a man seyn a &thorn;ing wi&thorn; bo&thorn;e his yen</L>
<L>&YOGH;it schul we wymmen visage it hardily</L>
<L>And wepe and swere and chide subtilly</L>
<L>So &thorn;at &yogh;e men schul ben as lewed as gees</L>
<L N="2276">what rekkith me of/ &yogh;our auctoritees</L>
<L>I wot wel &thorn;at &thorn;is Iew &thorn;is Salamon</L>
<L>Fond of vs wommen fooles many oon</L>
<L>But &thorn;ough he ne fond no good womman</L>
<L N="2280">&YOGH;et ha&thorn; &thorn;er founde many ano&thorn;er man
<PB REF="00000343.tif" N="331"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="472"></L>
<L>wommen ful trewe . ful good and vertuous</L>
<L>witnesse on hem &thorn;at duelle in cristes hous</L>
<L>with martirdom &thorn;ay proued her constaunce</L>
<L N="2284">The romayn gestes eek make remembraunce</L>
<L>Of many a verray trewe wyf also &middot;</L>
<L>But sire be nought wrath al be it so</L>
<L>Though &thorn;at he sayd he fond no good womman</L>
<L N="2288">I pray &yogh;ow tak &thorn;e sentens of &thorn;e man</L>
<L>he mente &thorn;us &thorn;at in souereign bounte</L>
<L>Nis noon but god &thorn;at sit in trinite</L>
<L>Ey for verrey god &thorn;at nys but oon</L>
<L N="2292">what make &yogh;e so moche of Salamon</L>
<L>what &thorn;ough he made a temple goddes hous</L>
<L>what &thorn;ough he were riche and glorious</L>
<L>So made he eek a temple of fals godis</L>
<L N="2296">How might he do a &thorn;ing &thorn;at more forbod is</L>
<L>Par de als fair as &yogh;e his name emplastre</L>
<L>he was a lecchour and an ydolastre</L>
<L>And in his eelde he verraily god forsook</L>
<L N="2300">And if god ne had as sai&thorn; &thorn;e book</L>
<L>I-spared him for his fadres sake he scholde</L>
<L>Haue left his regne ra&thorn;er &thorn;an he wolde<MILESTONE N="147a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>I sette right nought of &thorn;e vilonye</L>
<L N="2304">That &yogh;e of wommen write a boterflie</L>
<L>I am a womman needes most I speke</L>
<L>Or elles swelle til myn herte breke</L>
<L>For syn sche sayd &thorn;at we ben iangleresses</L>
<L N="2308">As euer hool I moote brouke my tresses</L>
<L>I schal not spare for no curtesye /</L>
<L>To speke him harm &thorn;at wold vs vilonye</L>
<L>Dame quod &thorn;is pluto be no lenger wroth</L>
<L N="2312">I &yogh;iue it vp but/ sith I swere myn oth</L>
<L>That I wil graunte him his sight agein</L>
<L>My word schal stonde I warne &yogh;ow certeyn</L>
<L>I am a kyng it sit me nought to lye</L>
<L N="2316">And I quod sche a queen of faierie
<PB REF="00000344.tif" N="332"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="473"></L>
<L>hir answer schal sche haue I vndertake</L>
<L>Let vs no mo wordes her-of make</L>
<L>For soth I wol no lenger &yogh;ow contrarie</L>
<L N="2320">&becaus; Now let vs turne agayn to Ianuarye</L>
<L>That in &thorn;is gardyn with &thorn;is faire may</L>
<L>Synge&thorn; ful merier &thorn;an &thorn;e papiniay</L>
<L>&YOGH;ow loue I best and schal and o&thorn;er noon</L>
<L N="2324">So long about &thorn;e aleys is he goon</L>
<L>Til he was come agaynes &thorn;ilke pirie</L>
<L>wher as &thorn;is damyan sittith ful mirye</L>
<L>On heigh among &thorn;e freische leeuys greene</L>
<L N="2328">This freissche may &thorn;at is so bright and scheene</L>
<L>Gan for to syke and sayd allas my syde</L>
<L>Now sir quod sche for ought &thorn;at may bityde</L>
<L>I most han of &thorn;e peres &thorn;at I see</L>
<L N="2332">Or I moot dye so sore longith me</L>
<L>To eten of &thorn;e smale peris greene</L>
<L>Help for hir loue &thorn;at is of heuen queene</L>
<L>I telle &yogh;ow wel a womman in my plyt</L>
<L N="2336">May haue to fruyt so gret an appetyt</L>
<L>&THORN;at sche may deyen . but sche it haue</L>
<L>Allas quod he &thorn;at I nad heer a knaue</L>
<L>That couthe clymbe allas allas quod he</L>
<L N="2340">For I am blynd . &yogh;e sire no fors quod sche<MILESTONE N="147b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>But wolde &yogh;e vouche sauf for goddes sake</L>
<L>The piry inwith &yogh;our armes for to take</L>
<L>For wel I woot &thorn;at &yogh;e mys-truste me</L>
<L N="2344">Than schold I clymbe wel y-nough quod sche</L>
<L>So I my foot might set vpon &yogh;our bak</L>
<L>Certes quod he &thorn;er on schal be no lak</L>
<L>Might I &yogh;ow helpe wi&thorn; myn herte blood</L>
<L N="2348">he stoupith doun and on his bak sche stood</L>
<L>And caught hir by a twist and vp sche goth</L>
<L>ladys I pray &yogh;ow &thorn;at &yogh;e be not wro&thorn;</L>
<L>I can not glose I am a rude man</L>
<L N="2352">And sodeinly anoon &thorn;is damyan
<PB REF="00000345.tif" N="333"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="474"></L>
<L>Gan pullen vp &thorn;e smok and in he throng</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;at pluto /saugh &thorn;is grete wrong</L>
<L>To Ianuary he &yogh;af his sight agayn</L>
<L N="2356">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ne was &thorn;er neuer man of &thorn;ing so fayn</L>
<L>But on his wif his &thorn;ought was euermo</L>
<L N="2360">Vp to &thorn;e tree he kest his ey&yogh;en tuo /</L>
<L>And seigh &thorn;at damyan his wyf had dressid</L>
<L>In which maner it may not ben expressid</L>
<L>But if I wolde speke vncurteisly</L>
<L N="2364">And vp he &yogh;af a roryng and a cry</L>
<L>As doth &thorn;e moder whan &thorn;e child schal dye</L>
<L>Out. help. allas. harrow. he gan to crie</L>
<L>O stronge lady stoure what dos &thorn;ow</L>
<L N="2368">And sche answerith sire what eylith &yogh;ow</L>
<L>haue paciens and resoun in &yogh;our mynde</L>
<L>I haue &yogh;ow holpen on bo&thorn;e &yogh;our eyen blynde</L>
<L>vp peril of my soule I schal not lyen</L>
<L N="2372">As me was taught to hele with &yogh;our yen</L>
<L>was no&thorn;ing bet. for to make &yogh;ow see</L>
<L>Than stroggle wi&thorn; a man vpon a tree</L>
<L>God woot I dede it in ful good entent</L>
<L N="2376">Stroggle quod he; &yogh;e algat in it went</L>
<L>God &yogh;iue &yogh;ow bo&thorn;e on schames deth to dyen</L>
<L>He swyued &thorn;e. I saugh it wi&thorn; myn yen</L>
<L>And elles be I honged by &thorn;e hals</L>
<L N="2380">Than is quod sche medicine fals<MILESTONE N="148a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>For certeynly if &thorn;at &yogh;e mighten see</L>
<L>&YOGH;e wold not say tho wordes vnto me</L>
<L>&YOGH;e han som glymsyng and no parfyt sight</L>
<L N="2384">I se quod he as wel as euer I might</L>
<L>Thankid be god wi&thorn; bo&thorn;e myn yen tuo</L>
<L>And by my trouth me &thorn;ought he did &thorn;e so</L>
<L>&YOGH;e. mase. mase. goode sire quod sche</L>
<L N="2388">This &thorn;ank haue I for I haue maad &yogh;ow see
<PB REF="00000346.tif" N="334"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="475"></L>
<L>Allas quod sche &thorn;at euer I was so kynde</L>
<L>Now dame quod he let al passe out of mynde</L>
<L>Com doun my leef and if I haue myssayd</L>
<L N="2392">God help me so as I am euel appayd</L>
<L>But by my fader soule I wende haue seyn</L>
<L>how &thorn;at &thorn;is damyan had by &thorn;e leyn</L>
<L>And &thorn;at &thorn;y smok had layn vpon &thorn;y brest</L>
<L N="2396">&YOGH;e sire quod sche &yogh;e may wene as &yogh;ow lest/</L>
<L>But sire a man &thorn;at wakith out of his slep</L>
<L>He may not sodeynly wel take keep</L>
<L>vpon a &thorn;ing ne seen it parfytly</L>
<L N="2400">Til &thorn;at he be adawed verrayly</L>
<L>Right so a man &thorn;at long ha&thorn; blynd I-be</L>
<L>Ne may not sodeynly so wel I-se</L>
<L>First whan &thorn;e sight is newe comen agayn</L>
<L N="2404">As he &thorn;at ha&thorn; a day or tuo I-sayn</L>
<L>Til &thorn;at &yogh;our sight y-stablid be a while</L>
<L>&THORN;er may ful many a sighte &yogh;ow bigile</L>
<L>Be&thorn; war I pray &yogh;ow for by heuen king</L>
<L N="2408">Ful many man wenith for to se a &thorn;ing</L>
<L>And it is al ano&thorn;er &thorn;an it/ semeth</L>
<L>he &thorn;at mys conceyueth he mys demeth</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word sche leep doun fro &thorn;e tre</L>
<L N="2412">This Ianuary who is glad but he</L>
<L>he kissith hir and clippith hir ful ofte</L>
<L>And on hir wombe he strokith hir ful ofte</L>
<L>And to his paleys hom he hath hir lad</L>
<L N="2416">Now goode men I pray &yogh;ow to be glad</L>
<L>Thus endith her my tale of Ianuarye</L>
<L>God blesse vs and his moder seinte marie / AmeN.<MILESTONE N="148b" UNIT="folio"></L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>&para; Here endith the marchauntes tale<NOTE>[Small break in MS.]</NOTE></TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000347.tif" N="335">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="476">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ey goddes mercy sayd our hoste &thorn;o</L>
<L N="2420">Now such a wyf I pray god keep me fro</L>
<L>lo whiche sleightes and subtilitees</L>
<L>In wommen ben for ay as busy as bees</L>
<L>Ben &thorn;ay vs seely men for to desceyue</L>
<L N="2424">And from a soth. euer wol &thorn;ay weyue</L>
<L>By this marchaundes tale it proueth wel</L>
<L>But douteles as trewe as eny steel</L>
<L>I haue a wyf &thorn;ough &thorn;at sche pore be</L>
<L N="2428">But of hir tonge a labbyng schrewe is sche</L>
<L>And &yogh;it sche hath an heep of vices mo</L>
<L>Ther-of no fors let alle such &thorn;inges go</L>
<L>But wite &yogh;e what in counseil be it seyd</L>
<L N="2432">Me rewith sore I am vnto hir teyd</L>
<L>And if I scholde reken euery vice</L>
<L>which &thorn;at sche hath I-wis I were to nyce</L>
<L>And cause why. it schuld reported be</L>
<L N="2436">And told to hir of som of &thorn;is meyne</L>
<L>Of whom it needith not for to declare</L>
<L>Syn wommen connen oute such chaffare</L>
<L>And eek my witte suffisith nought &thorn;erto</L>
<L N="2440">To tellen al wherfor my tale is do<NOTE PLACE="end">[No gap in the MS.]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="F" TYPE="group">

<PB REF="00000348.tif" N="336">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="478">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>F.</B> FRAGMENT VII.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; 1. THE SQUIRE'S HEAD-LINK.</HEAD>
<HEAD><B>HARLEIAN MS. 7334</B> (British Museum).</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&para; Sir Squier com for&thorn; . if &thorn;at &yogh;our wille be</L>
<L>And say vs a tale for certes &yogh;e</L>
<L>Connen &thorn;er-on as moche as ony man</L>
<L N="4">&para; Nay sire quod he . but I wil say as I can</L>
<L>wi&thorn; herty wil . for I wil not rebelle</L>
<L>Against &yogh;our wille . a tale wil I telle</L>
<L>Haue me excused if &thorn;at I speke amys</L>
<L N="8">My wil is good . and &thorn;erto my tale is this.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>&para; Her endith &thorn;e prologe<NOTE>[No break in the MS.]</NOTE></TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000349.tif" N="337">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="479">
<HEAD>&para; And her bygynneth &thorn;e Squyeres tale</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>AT Sarray in &thorn;e lond of Tartary<MILESTONE N="149a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ther dwelled a kyng &thorn;at werryed russy</L>
<L>Thurgh which &thorn;er deyed many a doughty man</L>
<L N="12">This nobil kyng was cleped Cambynskan</L>
<L>which in his tyme was of so gret renoun</L>
<L>That &thorn;er nas nowher in no regioun</L>
<L>So excellent a lord in alle &thorn;ing /</L>
<L N="16">Him lakked nought &thorn;at longed to a kyng</L>
<L>As of &thorn;e secte of which &thorn;at he was born</L>
<L>he kept his lawe . to which he was sworn</L>
<L>And &thorn;erto he was hardy wys and riche /</L>
<L N="20">And pitous and Iust alway yliche</L>
<L>Soth of his word benign and honurable</L>
<L>Of his corage as eny centre stable</L>
<L>&YOGH;ong freisch and strong in armes desirous</L>
<L N="24">As eny bachiler of al his hous</L>
<L>A fair person he was and fortunat</L>
<L>And kepte so wel his real astat</L>
<L>That &thorn;er was no wher such a ryal man</L>
<L N="28">This noble kyng &thorn;is tartre &thorn;is Cambynskan</L>
<L>hadde tuo sones by Elcheta his wyf</L>
<L>Of which &thorn;e eldest/ highte Algaryf</L>
<L>That o&thorn;er was I-cleped Samballo</L>
