<HEAD>GROUP <B>I.</B> FRAGMENT X.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; 1. THE BLANK-PARSON LINK.</HEAD>
<HEAD>&para; And here begynneth the prologe of &thorn;e Persouns tale</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>By &thorn;at &thorn;e maunciple had had his tale endid</L>
<L>The sonne fro &thorn;e south line is descendid</L>
<L>So lowe &thorn;at it nas nou&yogh;t to my sight</L>
<L N="4">Degrees [nyne and twenty as in hight<NOTE PLACE="marg">[In a later hand.]</NOTE>]</L>
<L>Ten on &thorn;e Clokke it was as I gesse /</L>
<L>For enleuen foote or litil more or lesse /</L>
<L>My schadow was at &thorn;ilk tyme of &thorn;e &yogh;ere</L>
<L N="8">Of which feet as my leng&thorn;e parted were /</L>
<L>In [sixe<NOTE PLACE="marg">[In a later hand.]</NOTE>] feet equal of proporcioun</L>
<L>Ther-with &thorn;e mones exaltacioun</L>
<L>In mena libra alway gan ascende</L>
<L N="12">As we were entryng at a townes ende</L>
<L>For which our host as he was wont to gye</L>
<L>As in &thorn;is caas our ioly compaignye</L>
<L>Sayd in &thorn;is wise lordings euerich oon</L>
<L N="16">Now lakke&thorn; vs no moo tales &thorn;an oon</L>
<L>Fulfilled is my sentens and my decre</L>
<L>I trowe &thorn;at we han herd of ech degre</L>
<L>Almost fulfilled is myn ordynaunce</L>
<L N="20">I pray to god so &yogh;eue him right good chaunce</L>
<L>That tellith to vs his tale lustily</L>
<L>Sire prest quod he artow a vicory<MILESTONE N="251b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Or artow a persoun say so&thorn; by &thorn;y fay</L>
<L N="24">Be what &thorn;ou be breke nought oure play
<PB REF="00000603.tif" N="591"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="590"></L>
<L>For euery man saue &thorn;ou hath told his tale</L>
<L>vnbocle and schew vs what is in &thorn;y male</L>
<L>For trewely me &thorn;inke&thorn; by &thorn;y chier</L>
<L N="28">&THORN;ou scholdist wel knyt vp a gret matier</L>
<L>Tel vs a tale anoon for cokkes boones</L>
<L>This persoun answerde al at oones /</L>
<L>Thow getist fable noon I-told for me</L>
<L N="32">For poul &thorn;at writes vnto thimothe</L>
<L>Repreue&thorn; hem &thorn;at weyue&thorn; sothfastnesse</L>
<L>And tellen fables and such wrecchednesse /</L>
<L>why schuld I sowen draf out of my fest/</L>
<L N="36">whan I may sowe whete if &thorn;at me lest/</L>
<L>For which I say if &thorn;at &yogh;ow lust to hiere</L>
<L>Moralite and vertuous matiere</L>
<L>And &thorn;anne &thorn;at &yogh;e wil &yogh;iue me audience</L>
<L N="40">I wol ful fayn at cristis reuerence</L>
<L>Do &yogh;ow plesaunce leful as I can</L>
<L>But truste&thorn; wel I am a suthern man</L>
<L>I can not geste. rum raf. ruf by letter</L>
<L N="44">Ne god wot rym hold I but litel better</L>
<L>And &thorn;erfor if &yogh;ow lust I wol not glose</L>
<L>I wol &yogh;ow telle a mery tale in prose /</L>
<L>To knyt vp al this fest and make an ende</L>
<L N="48">And Ih&umacr; for his grace wit me sende</L>
<L>To schewe &yogh;ow &thorn;e way in &thorn;is viage</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ilke parfyt glorious pilgrimage</L>
<L>That hatte Ierusalem celestial</L>
<L N="52">And if &yogh;e vouche sauf anoon I schal</L>
<L>Bygynne my tale for which I &yogh;ow pray</L>
<L>Telle &yogh;our avis I can no better say</L>
<L>But na&thorn;eles &thorn;is meditacioun</L>
<L N="56">I put it ay vnder correctioun</L>
<L>Of clerkes for I am not textuel</L>
<L>I take but &thorn;e sentens trusti&thorn; wel</L>
<L>Therfor I make protestacioun</L>
<L N="60">That I wol stonde to correccioun<MILESTONE N="252a" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000604.tif" N="592"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="591"></L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;is word we han assented soone</L>
<L>For as it semed it was for to done</L>
<L>To enden in som vertuous sentence</L>
<L N="64">And for to &yogh;eue him space and audience</L>
<L>And bad oure host he schulde to him say</L>
<L>That alle we to telle his tale him pray</L>
<L>Our host hadde &thorn;e wordes for vs alle</L>
<L N="68">Sir prest quod he now faire &yogh;ow bifalle</L>
<L>Say what &yogh;ow lust and we wil gladly hiere</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word he said in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>Telle&thorn; quod he &yogh;our meditacioun</L>
<L N="72">But hasteth &yogh;ow &thorn;e sonne wol a doun</L>
<L>Be&thorn; fructuous and &thorn;at / in litil space</L>
<L>And to do wel; God sende &yogh;ow grace /<NOTE PLACE="end">[No break in the MS.]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
